        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-09 15:28:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis could be a little stronger if we added const in a few more places. In fact if we just had: \n\n void (*hs_keycpy)(struct hlist_node *hnode, const void *key);\n\nand\n\n static inline void cfs_hash_keycpy(cfs_hash_t *hs, struct hlist_node *hnode, const void *key);\n\nThen the compiler would have rejected cfs_hash_keycpy(hs, new_key, hnode). Also the comment above the definition of hs_keycmp is backwards.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
